OL,5, As the passengers from Port-au-Prince  
OL,6, disembark at the bus terminal in       
OL,7, Cap-Haitien, the harrowing journey is  
OL,8, evident on their faces.                
OL,10,FThe trip out of the beleaguered Haitian
OL,11,Fcapital city involves running the      
OL,12,Fgauntlet along risky and dangerous     
OL,13,Froads, trying to avoid gunmen and      
OL,14,Fsporadic violence along the way.       
OL,16,F"It took us several hours longer than  
OL,17,Fit should as we had to reroute from the
OL,18,Fgang checkpoints along the way and     
OL,19,Fthere was gunfire", says one passenger,
OL,20,Fwho didn't give his name and was       
OL,21,Fclearly shaken by the experience.      
